caption: Yesterday was the first time we visited this place. But It is definitely not the last. We had great time with the efficient service, with the great  cuisine and wine and with the friendly charge. We will absolutely return there again.

Great cozy neighborhood spot. Food is a little hit or miss... sometimes amazing, sometimes mediocre. Ambience is great and they have made really nice COVID accommodations. The owner is often serving and could not be more lovely.
Great brunch 🙂  Every bite was bursting with flavor!
Great French food and warm atmosphere. Love their happy hour $1 oysters .
Loved the food. Very nice place.

Cute place, decent brunch food. They have some good little pods to eat in outside. Inside is small but they have a lot of dividers. Be careful crossing the bike lane as there is a lot of bike traffic here.

Service was fine... food was meh... they only accept american express or cash... 118.00 plus tip (20%) and amt fees.... nope.....its not 1998. Why the hell do you still only accept cash or american express?  There were only two tables filled at 730pm.... maybe it is time to update your p.o.s system and accept visa and mastercard.

Authentically French food and a nice ambiance. Came for brunch and ordered a croque monsieur, it came open-faced, but all the flavors were there. Side salad was nice and light, just like one you would get with a small entree in Paris.  Knocked one star for slower service and price - a bit on the expensive side compared to other restaurants in the area. As for service, they were all very lovely, but I asked for my bill and it took about 20min (plus a reminder) to actually get it and pay. I was not in a rush, hoever something to keep in mind if you are on a tight schedule.

The food was terrible and the service was terrible. It doesn’t matter if there is a pandemic! I asked for well done steak and I waited 45 mins and the steak was red raw. I ask for them to give either back and make it well done and they brought it back and taste like Charcoal. I told the waiter she told me this IS A FRENCH RESTAURANT. In which I dint understand why she said that. She made French restaurants sound bad because they don’t understand what well done meant. The waiters were super nice bu they need more workers. The bud guy was great!
Great friendly neighborhood restaurant. Food is always well done. Definitely our favorite comfort food spot!
The drinks and food were delicious (we had onion soups, endive salad, the burger, the chicken, the steak, the profiterole and the lava cake). Service was also great. We will come again!
Food and service was very good.

Great food, impeccable service, and they've done a fantastic job with their outdoor seating area. Everything felt safe, and yet the right tone for a relaxing evening dining outdoors. My husband and I stopped by as I was craving dessert (goes with the times) and wanted to grab something to-go so as not to take up a table. They were super sweet and offered us a space to sit down and enjoy it. We ended up having some wine, and their homemade chocolate cake with fresh coconut ice cream was insane (aka: AMAZING). Really lovely people there, highly recommend for a great night out at a neighborhood spot.

Excellent brunch. Everyone enjoyed nearly everything from the Croque Monsieur to le tartine d'olivier. The only  reason we dropped a star is because we ordered pork sausage and were told we were served chicken sausage. Also the merguez sausage(s) while delicious... were lost in the huge amount of bagette, The equivalent of a 6 inch hotdog cut in 2 lengthwise and served on 9 inch bagette. We were also   like to point out the outdoor dining is almost exclusively in the shade which while good on hot days was brutal on the coldest day of the summer.
Nice place
My favorite French food in Brooklyn, owner is really nice, staff is super attentive.

Last week was our first time we visited this magnificent restaurant. But It is no doubt not the last. We had great time with the attentive service, with the superb  cuisine and fine drinks and with the decent charge. We will no doubt return there again.
Charming, authentic, and delicious

I’ve been coming here 2+ times a week for almost four years. There is nothing that I wouldn’t recommend—and I’ve had everything. If you’re wondering why I haven’t posted a review until now, it’s because I didn’t want all of you to discover it, which I now realize is mean. Fantastic, authentic French food, owned and staffed by good people. See you soon.
Great food, vibe and service always. We've been going to Olivier's since it opened and it never disappoints.
After the lovely service at the to-go window this morning, I'll stop by on my way to work every day I'm in the area! Thanks for that croissant!
We love Olivier Bistro . This a true neighborhood’s gem. Delicious authentic french bistro food. Cozy atmosphere and friendly service.

Atmosphere calm, food delicious, friendly staff. All around great place. Took my mother here for her birthday, the whole family loved it. Highly recommend! Very hip for my fellow mallenials (ie great happy hour special on some yum cocktails). Best French I’ve had in park slope.

Eh.. food was ok. Service was terrible. The server seemed more in to reading her book than being attentive. We sat there almost 40 mins waiting for our food. She didn't even come over once to check on us.. no updates on when our food would be out.. not even a glance over to see if we needed more coffee or water. This isn't a bad review. Just not a very inviting experience

I've had Olivier Bistro here three times now and it is always a disappointment. The food never matches the menu description ("fried goat cheese" doesn't mean raw goat cheese on a piece of bread) and they are consistently out of menu items, giving replacements you don't ask for.  Go to the Peruvian place around the corner, the quinoa is better anyway.
I always enjoy this place.  Great food, delightful waitress, good times.
It was alright for the price. The service was slow although we were the only customers. Wouldn't come again.
Thought it would be better.  Brunch was fine, service kind of awkward
Great neighborhood bistro. The food is very good as are the cocktails.
Frozen food!!

Please ignore the negative reviews, this is a marvelous restaurant.  Visiting and our hotel was close and we happened upon this place, checked out the reviews and decided to give it a go.   The service, the food and the ambience were first rate.  A very enjoyable evening out.
Very sweet little restaurant. The kids loved their burgers.
Dee-Li-Cious!!
Cash only

This place is a shame to the French cuisine. There were no clients there and I had to wait 40 min for my order when it finally came, the french fries were old like from the day before worst than Macdonalds french fries, the steak was horrible! In addition they hit me with a high bill! This spoiled my day the worst decision I made in a long time! If they continue with such horrible service pretty soon they will be out of business.
A wonderful little restaurant with very tasty fare at very fair prices. A perfect neighborhood place.
Perfect French lunch, from cheese and escargot through dessert.
We stopped in for a coffee and a beer. Impolite, slow service. Pretty much the only people in there so really no excuse.
Great food and wonderful atmosphere.

Stopped in for a Sunday brunch. It's a very nice little place with tables inside and outside. The food was outstanding. Really top notch. And the staff were very friendly. They only accept American Express or cash, but there is an ATM in the restaurant.
Food is good. Serving is kind of slow. Dishes seem to be made-to-order so this is fine.
Our food came in 50 minutes, location isn't giving you a pleasant atmosphere and inside the restaurant smells bad. Liver pate had to much black pepper, but over all was good.
Its is not good at all. There is better places to Eat French food in Brooklyn and NYC. It is disgusting...
Good service

I Love this Place.  Everything I tried here is Delicious.  The Steak Frittes Delicious.  The Burger Superb.  Onion Soap and Escargots Yummy.   But the Absolute Best is their mini Chocolate cake with Coconut Ice Cream.  It is really Out Of this World.  They have a full bar also and Brunch Specials.  The Staff is Very Nice and Helpful.  This place is a GEM.
No American flag How can you put up two foreign flags without putting up at least one American flag whatever happened to flag etiquette see there is such a thing you know
Very nice summer seating arrangement, good food and drinks. Nice for a quiet day date.
Web site lies about the prix fixe menu being available.
This place is seriously bad. If it was a neighborhood bistro with neighborhood prices it would be acceptable. As it is it’s a really bad dinner experience with seriously mediocre food.
Good enough

Solid authentic French food although quality is somewhat inconsistent and the menu is limited so it doesn’t make sense to revisit often. The restaurant is a bit cramped when busy as there isn’t a lot of space. Also, for some reason they only take Amex and cash, no other credit cards. This makes me think twice before coming so hopefully this will change in the future.
Food was ok, not the best. They only take Amex and cash.
Food is really delicious. The service is great
Food was amazing, service pleasant, will definitely be back!
Great, cozy spot... but the food really isn't worthwhile.  The only good things are the moules frites.
Very intimate, comfortable setting. Last 2x I went, I had brunch and stayed for dinner. Best Croque Madame and salad ever!
Remember this.. It's cash only! If you go in expecting to pay with a card.. American Express only! Other than that.. Beautiful inside.. Breakfast was great... But French toast and eggs.. $23 😒
Very warm, friendly, and personable atmosphere, the service is exceptional. The food tastes amazing.
The best French toast I've ever had, but the brisket toast was soggy and cold
I love French food and this is classic French in every sense. Well done, France!
Great atmosphere! Yummy food!

Olivier Bistro is a French restaurant. It is not German, it is not Brazilian, it is not Peruvian, it is not Spanish, it is not French-Canadian, it is not Mexican, it is not Chinese, it is not Japanese, it is not Italian, it if not Moroccan, it is not any other country’s cruise but French. In case you were curious.
Delicious food. Amen.
Great food. Amazing Valentine's day deal. Can't miss.
Like the good the service is bad
Best onion soups I have ever had. Finally a chef who actually knew what medium rare meant. Service was extremely good. Great vibes.
Excellent food, drinks and service!
I heard the bloodiest were good here.  I agreed! Didn't have any food, but it looked and smelled good.
Cote de beouf was more like a great steak. But that's the point it was a great steak. Cocktails are solid. Can't wait to head back and explore more of the menu.

The first morning of the snow season in New York in 2017.... I went to this tiny cozy and quiet coffee shop in the middle of Brooklyn. I felt very welcomed in that warmth place. The coffee wasn’t the best but It was the first one I had during my first visit to New York.

Solid little french bistro. Well executed breakfast options. Won't go wrong with standbys here. French toast, steak frites, etc. Pate is solid if not mind blowing. Tartin was satisfying (see photo). Service is pleasant, wait staff is actually French. I might even come back in just to see if the escargot is legit.
Food was so-so yet expensive.  A field green salad was just lettuce in a bowl with a little dressing, and NOTHING else.  I would skip it.
Intimate setting, excellent food and personable service, French

(Translated by Google) Very cozy and nice place. The food, whether French or not, is excellent and the wine list, while expensive, is well stocked. The waitress is superb and the reception of quality, do not hesitate!  (Original) Endroit très cosy et sympa. La nourriture, qu'on soit français ou pas, est excellente et la carte des vins, bien que chère, est bien fournie. La serveuse est superbe et l'accueil de qualité, n'hésitez pas !
Good food, a little cramped but worth the wait for the food. Try the eggs norvingienn.

I'm a delivery driver with Uber Eats and GrubHub and this restaurant is so slow when it comes to the food now I have never tasted your food so I can't comment on that but I can only comment on the fact that the place is small and then you wait such a long time for your food
The best rib eye steak I ever had.

Food was tasty and if the service wasn't so painfully slow I might consider eating there again but everything was mind numbingly slow from the water, to ordering, waiting for food, clearing food and check.  All in all it was almost three hours for...decent food nothing special. They need a new server. It's a small restaurant no reason to be so ignored.
Pretty good food, slow service. Expect to be here 2.5+ hours

The staff was nice. The place was quaint. It had a vacation feel for me. This could be because we were on vacation and we don't have quaint places like this where I am from. It was a nice experience. Not much in the gluten free, dairy free, etc... But I can't imagine small places having the room for the extra inventory. I would recommend this place.
Was expecting at least some lettuce in the lamb sandwich, but instead I got just bread with mustard and a sausage.
Beautiful restaurant, feels like a bistro in Paris. Delicious food and friendly staff. Everything is amazing!
Cash only or AMEX is annoying. Other than that, the food is excellent and reasonably priced. I particularly enjoyed the french toast, mussels, and appletini.

Accommodated Saturday brunch for 20 albeit cozy. Nice decor with open dining. Food was very good to excellent. Hostess were courteous and easy on the eyes. Best French Toast ever!  Prices were reasonable.  Worth your time and money.
Mondays 2-for-1 wine; great atmosphere, friendly staff.
Great staff, wonderful food at decent prices
Delicious food. Escargots were great. Would also recommend the duck breast. Yummy!
Wery tasty restaurant. Good service. They don't exept regular credit cards. And it's is not cheap.
Great European cafe feel and great food.
I had the prix fixe lunch menu. French Onion Soup Seared Salmon it was really well prepared.
Very nice experience. The staff was very attentive and helpful. Would highly recommend this restaurant.
Came for Brunch. It was delicious.
Nice cafe, nice staff, good food..
What kind of restaurant only accepts American Express? This one. It's 2018, if you want cash you can pay the ATM fee. The food isn't event that great and the service is slow

Lunch here today was absolutely fabulous. An enormous piece of delightfully cooked salmon over some kind of delicious sprouts and mushrooms I think.  A really good salad.  Cappuccino and a glass of Sauvignon Blanc.  Yum.

Strolling through the neighborhood I passed by and decided to try it out as they had two outside seating spots available. I'm glad that I did! They had a great brunch menu at reasonable prices and was craving a Bloody Mary which they also had. French Bistro, feel and charm, the owner and his little Daughter were on hand to great us and seat us. Server was a charming and friendly young lady. Ordered and received our food in a timely matter. The Bloody Mary was fantastic and not watered down, the Eggs Benedict with Salmon was just right, the egg oozing out with a light cut through it and the Hollandaise Sauce was smooth and not too thick. Came with three Steak Fries with it's own spiced sauce which was an perfect accompaniment and amount. Also had the Croquet on Toast with an egg on top and mixed greens. The toast was a burned on the bottom, but it was still a tasty dish and didn't want to be too picky as we were hungry.  Only thing I'd have wished for was to be checked on a bit more for a refill of the drinks (only had one drink each) as we were never asked if we wanted any more to drink (empty glasses). But I guess it was luckily a good thing to pass on as we were satisfied with the meal overall and plan on going back for their Sunday $1 Oysters...

The food is fantastic I have been a few times for brunch and I always get the French toast so I may not have the widest knowledge of the menu but every time I go everyone enjoys what they ordered so I stand by my statement. And staff is very friendly!
Omg amazing Sunday brunch!!!
Today I had the pleasure of dining here as a field trip-the food, service and atmosphere was amazing altogether-Au Revoir!

Food was great Chef did a really good job with creating traditionally french bistro food. Service was fine until we were told they don't accept Visa but we can use their ATM that charges $2.25. NYC restaurants need to stop pushing the cost of transactions on their customer.
Cute and small bistro with a real French vibe. We went for brunch and all the components of the dish were cooked properly with very good ingredients. Also the lava cake was delish!!!
Wonderful place. Great food and beverage attentive staff.
The food is great!!  Love the hours, French toast, and steak frites.
(Translated by Google) Excellent  (Original) Excelente
Best lunch special! Delicious fresh food
Great French dishes and techniques. Brunch is phenomenal.
Get the escargot
Nice atmosphere and food was delicious, just a bit overpriced. Dinner for 2, 1 shared app, 2 drinks and shared dessert... $180.

Very mediocre french fare at too high a price point. The Molleaux Chocolat (essentially a Lava cake) was a stale brownie. Server eventually acknowdged it wasnt as advertised but didnt volunteer to take it off the bill.
Delicious food and very accommodating for a short notice group of 6.
Very cute French bistro with an excellent brunch/breakfast menu!
Nice neighborhood french bistro. The owner is great, he's always there and really cares about the place. The food is delicious, classic dishes done very well. They serve a nice burger too.

Excellent little restaurant. The menu is small, which is great. The food simple and well done. The service is excellent, unobtrusive yet prompt and diligent.  We went for a brunch most recently. I had a simple steak and eggs, which was well seasoned and cooked exactly as ordered. My bloody Mary was appropriately spicy and strong enough to notice. My partner's croque madame was on a generous portion of sourdough and done perfectly without any unnecessary flourishes.  The only downside to our meal was the noise. The dining room is very small and one very loud table can dominate the space with noise. That was unfortunately the case on our last visit, but not the fault of the restaurant so much as the fault of the table of primary a school teachers who struggled with using their "inside voices".
My favourite French food option in park slope.
Great experience
Incredibly delicious! Cappuccino was perfectly made, and the mini desserts assortment was out of this world. Friendly staff. Great date spot. Highly recommend.
Love the atmosphere
such a delight to have dinner here. service was personal and friendly, environment was warm, and the food was exceedingly good.
Quaint, authentic French experience with Excellent Food.
Love it, Sinserite house wine beef and escargots...boom
Great place to eat
Their steak absolutely melts in your mouth it is that well hung. Great wines too. The fries were an instant hit with both kids and parents. The creme brulée is to die for!
Love this place! Amazing brunch!
Love the place. Parisian atmosphere and great bite
Very cozy, good wine, excellent, friendly service.
Food was good. 7 dollars for a side of fries...
Friendly french staff, beautiful meals, cozy atmosphere
Friendly hard working staff. You can ask any employee questions about the food and they are well informed. The food is pricey but it's worth it.
Excellent food, great brunch spot! Authentic French experience with French staff and cuisine. Took a little for the food to come, but well worth it. Fresh juices are fantastic
The food was good but I don't find it acceptable to be told that they only accept AMEX at the end of my meal.
Great brunch. A little loud.
Friendly if a bit inconsistent food.  Classic atmosphere.
Super french bistro with live music. Good service, good burger, good times!
It was just okay.
Great food, great atmosphere and the staff was exceptional

(Translated by Google) It's perfect !!!! Thank you so much.  (Original) C' este parfait!!!! Merci beaucoup.

Decent food.....authentic French waitress....couldn't seem to be bothered getting our food...one customer at bar,,maybe her bf kept her attention....no other customers but our trio...and had to remind her to get our food ...condiments.drinks etc..totally annoying.....
Love the coffee window

Can't say enough good things.  Food was fabulous, tasty, well prepared and sufficient portions.  The staff was really nice.  Just the right amount of attention, while allowing us to feel relaxed, not rushed at all. I highly recommend and will certainly be returning.
Great atmosphere, authentic service, good food.

Olivier Bistro is our favorite restaurant in Brooklyn.  We have been coming consistently since they opened and have always had a delightful experience.  We even celebrated our engagement and hosted our rehearsal dinner for our wedding at Olivier.  We have tried nearly every menu item and each one is better than the next.  Although we love the fare and old-fashioners, what we really love most are the staff who know us by name and even wave to us when we pass the restaurant running errands around the neighborhood.
A bit over priced for the quality of the food. It was ok. Sparkling water  $7 - give me a break. We waiting 25 mins for food and we were the only ones in there

Me, my husband and our friends had dinner here. It was the first time for all of us and we all enjoyed it.  We had oysters, salmon tartar, crispy risotto, Brussels sprouts, hanger steak, and duck and all of it was delicious. French onion soup awesome !!! The drinks where also very good !! I would so come back here again. The waitress was so friendly and amazing. The environment was also very relaxed and welcoming.

I really wanted to like this place, but I left feeling annoyed and hungry. My husbands food was fairly good, but my moules frites were a far cry from delicious. I didn't want to ruin the night so I pulled out the massive mussel beards myself until I got down to the last 1/3 of the pot and the entire mussel shell was full of grit. A pile of dirt. The fries were off white and limp. I should have sent it all back. We may have had an off experience, but I don't think I could get excited to try again.
Delicious French meals from different regions.

Great small bistro!  It was surprise find in South Slope.  The drink were great, the food fantastic and overall experience was enjoyable.  My only regret was not getting there early enough to enough the happy hour oyster and wine special.
what an authentic paris experience! french staff, delicious food and great wine. it's on 4th ave, but worth the walk no matter where you are in the slope. it's a must go for brunch or dinner!
The food here every time is amazing. It's a cozy place with great atmosphere. I keep going back!
A gem in the raw! For a true French bistrot experience in the heart of Brooklyn.
superb food & atmosphere, reasonably priced bottles of wine, very friendly staff. great place to be a regular
Excellent coffee with a cozy atmosphere. French onion soup is on point.
